The decision to use the **38th parallel** as a temporary division led to the **permanent split of Korea** into North and South after World War II, a division that persists today. The Soviet Union occupied the north, while the U.S. controlled the south, eventually leading to two separate nations. This division was formalized in 1948 with the establishment of the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (North) and the Republic of Korea (South).
